Si to 250 ppm as\nmeasured by secondary ion mass spectrometry. The impurity content and the\ncrystallization kinetics via solid phase epitaxy are discussed. The $^{28}$Si\nlayer is confirmed to be a single crystal using transmission electron\nmicroscopy. This method of Si isotopic enrichment shows promise for\nincorporating into the fabrication process flow of Si spin qubit devices.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Sep 2020 02:34:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-13"}
