 star evolved from the ZAMS, which is a\nlittle younger than the ages deduced for many cool giants. We also detected the\n$\\lambda$\\,6707-\\AA~lithium line in the spectrum of the giant component, thus\nadding to the evidence that it is near the start of its primary ascent of the\nred-giant branch.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Sep 2020 05:06:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-04"}
