pse underestimate the intensity of the\ngas emission by up to several factors towards the only protostellar core in our\nsample, indicating that different dynamics take place in different evolutionary\ncore stages. If the LP model is confirmed towards a larger sample of prestellar\ncores, it would indicate that they may form by compression or accretion of gas\nfrom larger scales. If the QE-BES model is confirmed, it means that quasi\nhydrostatic cores can exist within turbulent ISM.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Sep 2020 14:26:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-04"}
